236
00:16:56,940 --> 00:16:58,780
Miss Undine!

237
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:04,610
Mr. Patissier!

238
00:17:05,450 --> 00:17:07,690
You're going to reopen your shop?

239
00:17:07,690 --> 00:17:09,950
Yes, and it's all thanks to you.

240
00:17:14,430 --> 00:17:16,160
They're so cute!

241
00:17:16,160 --> 00:17:21,070
Remember how you said you felt sorry for
the chocolates when the bottle broke?

242
00:17:21,570 --> 00:17:25,160
When I heard that, I thought...

243
00:17:26,470 --> 00:17:28,910
"I want to make my customers smile."

244
00:17:29,310 --> 00:17:32,310
Those chocolates were made
with love, so it's sad...

245
00:17:32,310 --> 00:17:34,650
