247
00:17:38,920 --> 00:17:41,520
Chocolates made with love...

248
00:17:41,520 --> 00:17:45,490
Yes. I was able to remember that, thanks to you.

249
00:17:45,490 --> 00:17:48,360
I thought you had closed your shop for good.

250
00:17:49,300 --> 00:17:51,400
Sorry for making you worry.

251
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:58,630
I was trying to come up with another way to make
people smile, and a better method of sharing it.

252
00:17:58,910 --> 00:18:02,030
Then, yesterday it hit me.

253
00:18:02,640 --> 00:18:05,680
What if I used all sorts of
different wrapping papers?

254
00:18:05,680 --> 00:18:09,240
Sort of like how there are all sorts
of different buildings in this city.

255
00:18:09,320 --> 00:18:15,660
Ah, is that why you were at Ca' d'Oro
and Ponte dell' Accademia yesterday?

256
00:18:15,660 --> 00:18:19,860
It seems like you always catch me
at the most unflattering moments.

257
00:18:19,860 --> 00:18:25,430
Yeah. When I'm out of ideas,
I walk around the city until I get tired.

258
00:18:25,430 --> 00:18:28,960
When I do that, somehow it's easier
to come up with something good.

259
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,110
Neo-Venezia gives you hints, doesn't it?

260
00:18:33,110 --> 00:18:37,980
Please, pick any two you like,
for you and your cat.

261
00:18:37,980 --> 00:18:39,550
Eh? But...

262
00:18:39,550 --> 00:18:41,840
Take it as a token of my appreciation.

263
00:18:43,280 --> 00:18:44,750
Okay...

264
00:18:44,750 --> 00:18:46,650
Thank you very much.

265
00:18:46,650 --> 00:18:50,020
Then, I'll take this one, and this one...

266
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:55,330
Ah... It feels like such a waste
to even open the wrapping!

267
00:18:55,330 --> 00:18:59,270
Don't say that. I'd feel sorry for the
chocolates if you didn't eat them.

268
00:18:59,500 --> 00:19:01,060
You're right.

269
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,640
I know!

270
00:19:02,640 --> 00:19:08,130
It's still a little early to set up shop,
so may I treat you two to a caffè latte?

271
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:24,020
No matter how often you come here,
it's still beautiful, isn't it?

272
00:19:24,020 --> 00:19:29,790
Yeah. I always stop by Caffè Florian
after I close my shop.

273
00:19:30,300 --> 00:19:34,790
When I look at the paintings,
it somehow puts me at ease.

274
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:38,310
It really does, doesn't it?

275
00:19:38,310 --> 00:19:39,860
Hello.

276
00:19:41,240 --> 00:19:43,440
Ah, hello!

277
00:19:43,810 --> 00:19:45,970
You're the gentleman who's always here...

278
00:19:46,250 --> 00:19:48,770
Do you two know each other?

279
00:19:49,650 --> 00:19:52,550
He's the owner of this café.

280
00:19:52,550 --> 00:19:55,820
Eh, really?! I had no idea!

281
00:19:58,190 --> 00:20:00,930
Do you like the paintings in here?

282
00:20:00,930 --> 00:20:04,430
Yes. Every painting is magnificent.

283
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:13,670
This entire café, interior and all, was dismantled
and brought over before Venice was submerged.

284
00:20:13,670 --> 00:20:16,870
All the paintings are the originals from back then.

285
00:20:17,180 --> 00:20:19,740
So they're that old...

286
00:20:20,410 --> 00:20:22,750
You must take very good care of them.

287
00:20:22,880 --> 00:20:26,450
Well, these paintings belong here, after all.

288
00:20:26,450 --> 00:20:28,080
They belong here?

289
00:20:29,960 --> 00:20:35,000
It's just a simple phrase, but there's
a lot of meaning in those words.

290
00:20:35,000 --> 00:20:35,960
Yeah.

291
00:20:38,430 --> 00:20:39,920
I see...

292
00:20:40,230 --> 00:20:45,770
The things people create are filled with
the emotion of their makers.

293
00:20:45,770 --> 00:20:48,540
That's why they get passed down, don't they?

294
00:20:48,940 --> 00:20:52,640
They're cherished, and they belong...

295
00:20:53,980 --> 00:20:56,680
Your chocolates are the same way, Anri!

296
00:20:57,520 --> 00:21:00,350
Whether it's a big building
or a small bundle of chocolates,

297
00:21:00,350 --> 00:21:03,660
they're both the same because
they were made with love!

298
00:21:03,660 --> 00:21:06,460
That's why they make everyone smile!

299
00:21:07,860 --> 00:21:09,330
I see...

300
00:21:09,330 --> 00:21:13,960
Then, if my chocolates become
something that belongs in this city...

301
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:18,800
I'm sure they will! They'll be
something wonderful that belongs here!

302
00:21:21,610 --> 00:21:24,300
Thank you. I'll do my best.

303
00:21:26,650 --> 00:21:32,220
Then, in celebration of
Neo-Venezia's newest addition,

304
00:21:32,220 --> 00:21:36,690
may I treat you to some of
Caffè Florian's special cioccolata?

305
00:21:36,690 --> 00:21:38,180
Yay!

306
00:21:38,460 --> 00:21:40,050
Thank you very much.

307
00:21:42,430 --> 00:21:44,500
Thank you for treating us.

308
00:21:44,500 --> 00:21:46,060
Thank you very much.

309
00:21:48,440 --> 00:21:50,960
Please come back anytime.

310
00:21:51,040 --> 00:21:53,230
